In the 1950s, multiple hypothesis testing began to gain attraction, especially for high-throughput data analysis, where the problem of multiple comparisons was particularly outstanding. Microarray data is an example of high-dimensional data, which is characterized by small sample size and high variable dimension, which constituted a typical multiple hypothesis testing problem. Table 1 summarizes this situation in traditional form.
